OL,3,CBattle of the Imjin River: Calls for
OL,4,Cpermanent memorial for local troops
OL,6,FThe families of Gloucestershire troops
OL,7,Fwho fought in the 1951 Battle of the
OL,8,FImjin River in South Korea have called
OL,9,Ffor a memorial to them in the Forest
OL,10,Fof Dean.
OL,12,FHundreds of them took part in the
OL,13,Fconflict, which is also known as the
OL,14,FBattle of Solma-ri or Battle of
OL,15,FGloster Hill, in South Korea.
OL,17,FFor four days, the Chinese People's
OL,18,FVolunteer Army attacked United Nations
OL,19,FCommand positions on the lower Imjin
OL,20,FRiver in an attempt to recapture the
OL,21,FSouth Korean capital Seoul.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/10
