OL,6,FThe Gloucestershire Regiment was
OL,7,Fvastly outnumbered by Chinese and
OL,8,FNorth Korean forces. Among them were
OL,9,F15 young men from the Forest of Dean.
OL,11,FThe British Army Museum has described
OL,12,Fit as "the bloodiest engagement
OL,13,Fendured by the British Army since the
OL,14,FSecond World War."
OL,16,FDave Gardiner, from Ruardean in the
OL,17,FForest of Dean, was just 20 years old
OL,18,Fwhen he went to war. Though he
OL,19,Fsurvived the battle, he was captured
OL,20,Fand held in a prisoner-of-war camp for
OL,21,Fyears.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/10
