OL,6,FDave's brother Andrew said: "I waved
OL,7,Fhim off in 1950 and I met him four
OL,8,Fyears later when they returned. He'd
OL,9,Fbeen so ill-treated in the prison camp.
OL,11,F"A lot of them would never speak about
OL,12,Fit. But Dave would. He would tell you
OL,13,Fif you wanted to know. He would tell
OL,14,Fyou each and every aspect of it.
OL,16,F"I think you can judge somebody by the
OL,17,Fpeers around him. They regarded him -
OL,18,Fit's very difficult to talk about -
OL,19,Fthey regarded him as the bravest of
OL,20,Fthe brave. So do I."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
