OL,6,FRoy's son Andrew said: "They were in
OL,7,Fthe brunt of the fighting right at the
OL,8,Ffront. And the stories my Dad told me
OL,9,Fabout it - they were so brave and I
OL,10,Fjust think they should be recognised
OL,11,Fmore."
OL,13,FThe memorial was inspired by the
OL,14,Farchway Roy, Dave and the other
OL,15,Fprisoners of war passed through on
OL,16,Ftheir way to freedom. Andrew Gardiner
OL,17,Fhelped design it in his brother's
OL,18,Fmemory.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/10
